#ol:
  [#*:

    zstring - leads with size: variable length encoded uint where bit 8 of each
    byte is the continuation bit (when set). Size is number of bytes in string
    (excl null terminator and size bytes), not the number of chars. Then UTF8
    encoded string, then null terminated. Can convert to a (readonly) C string
    by taking a pointer after the size bytes.

    All string literals in the source are zstrings?
  ]
